<dl id="n36193b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36193b">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36193b"> 193(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pomatum candle</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Their hair, untortured by the abominations of art, was scrupulously <mark>pomatumed</mark> back from their foreheads <mark>with a candle</mark>, and covered with a little cap of quilted calico, which fitted exactly to their heads. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 103</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
